#### `src/wow/protocol/guild.test.ts` - Packet Parser Tests
- Tests for `GuildMemberStatus` enum constants
- Tests for `parseGuildRoster()` - expects PacketReader, returns member list
- Tests for `parseGuildQueryResponse()` - expects PacketReader, returns guild metadata
- Tests for `buildGuildQuery()` - expects uint32 guild ID, returns Uint8Array packet body
- All tests verify consuming all bytes with `.remaining === 0`

#### `src/wow/world-handlers.test.ts` - Guild Handler Tests (Lines 3232-3396)
```typescript
describe("guild handlers", () => {
  function buildGuildRosterPacket(): Uint8Array { ... }
  function buildGuildQueryResponsePacket(): Uint8Array { ... }

  test("SMSG_GUILD_ROSTER populates guildStore", async () => {
    const guildReady = new Promise<GuildEvent>((resolve) => {
